        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">One thing about ST - if you have a DoT on the mob you ST...it's going to place you on top of the hate list. Your name is still attached to that DoT, but all the damage from tanks/nukers/pets are going to be forgotten. This includes the Darkness line of spells - most people forget this is a DoT...not just a snare.</P><P>Also, if an enchanter wants to mez a ST'd mob...all they have to do is Stun it first then mez to their heart's content.</P><P>I've used ST several times to clear aggro from an nuke-happy enchanter...stuns the mob until the tank hits it (which I find hilarious...me saving one of the holy trinity's asses with my lame-ass mez).</P><P>- Ryptor, Necromancer 52nd level on Tunare </P><P>** Alas, poor Jabober, I knew him well... **<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
